<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,982,1369]" box="[151,1173,982,1009]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,982,1008]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Description.</emphasis>
Slender species with uniform whitish emerald green coloration (
<figureCitation box="[1023,1161,982,1009]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–47" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1997,2021]" captionTargetBox="[176,1408,535,1967]" captionTargetId="figure-133@11.[174,1412,525,1974]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 29–47. Macropsis spp., lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4404167" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4404167/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Figs. 44–45</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,982,1369]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
Abdominal apodemes of 2 
<superScript attach="left" box="[493,509,1018,1032]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">nd</superScript>
tergite in male wide, parallel-sided, usually of equal width and length, separated by very narrow notch (
<figureCitation box="[374,472,1055,1081]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 198</figureCitation>
), sternal apodemes of similar shape, but longer, with angular tips, separated by wider notch (
<figureCitation box="[228,327,1091,1117]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Fig. 199</figureCitation>
). Penis stem in side view narrow, usually, bent at almost right angle, as in 
<figureCitation box="[1154,1342,1091,1117]" captionStart="FIGURES 165–203" captionStartId="21.[151,264,1867,1891]" captionTargetBox="[207,1381,183,1840]" captionTargetId="figure-16@21.[205,1382,181,1843]" captionText="FIGURES 165–203. Macropsis aselae sp. n. (165–182), M. illota (183–189), M. sibirica (190–195), M. megerlei (196), M. emeljanovi (197), M. elaeagni (198–199), and M. scabrosa (200–203). 165–167, 183–184, 190–191, 198, 201―male abdominal apodemes of the 2nd tergite; 168–171, 185–186, 192, 199, 202—the 2nd sternite; 172–174, 187–188, 193–194, 196–197, 200―penis, lateral view; 175–177―pygofer process, lateral view; 178–179―style; 180–182, 189, 195, 203―the 2nd valvulae of ovipositor." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4457948" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4457948/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Figs. 196–197. 2</figureCitation>
<superScript attach="left" box="[1342,1358,1090,1104]" fontSize="6" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">nd</superScript>
valvulae of ovipositor with 3–5 preapical teeth each.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,982,1369]" box="[199,942,1162,1190]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
Body length (including tegmina): 
<specimenCount box="[580,603,1163,1189]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
