<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="395" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,982,1369]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1234,1260]" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Distribution.</emphasis>
Western Europe, European 
<collectingCountry box="[665,740,1235,1261]" name="Russia" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Russia</collectingCountry>
(northwards as far as 
<collectingRegion box="[985,1086,1235,1261]" country="Russia" name="Moscow" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Moscow</collectingRegion>
), Caucasus, Transcaucasia, 
<collectingCountry name="Kazakhstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, and Central Asia from 
<collectingCountry box="[518,673,1271,1297]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
to Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[800,934,1271,1297]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
. Widely introduced with ornamental oleaster (
<taxonomicName box="[161,423,1307,1333]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Elaeagnaceae" genus="Elaeagnus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="14" pageNumber="395" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustifolia">
<emphasis box="[161,423,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Elaeagnus angustifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) far beyond natural range which is hardly possible to reconstruct now. In Southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,282,1343,1369]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="395">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
almost everywhere on oleaster in the foothills and plains.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
